# PyInstaller build output
build/
dist/
*.spec

# Python cache files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# Virtual environments (if you ever add one)
venv/
.env/

# VS Code settings (optional — remove this if you want to share your editor config)
.vscode/

# Windows junk
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
```

Create a file called `.gitignore` in the root of your project folder and paste that in.

The general rule for what goes on GitHub is: **only include things a user needs to run your project, or that you wrote yourself**. Generated files, build artifacts, and caches can always be recreated so they just add noise.

Your repo should end up looking like:
```
ao3-epub-to-odt/
├── scripts/
│   └── ao3_to_odt.py
├── gui.py
├── launch.bat
├── .gitignore
└── README.md